# Coding Standards

## TypeScript Guidelines
- Always use proper TypeScript types
- Avoid `any` type unless absolutely necessary
- Use interfaces for complex data structures
- Enable strict type checking

## React/Next.js Best Practices
- Use functional components with hooks
- Implement proper error boundaries
- Use Next.js built-in features for optimization
- Keep components small and focused
- Use proper prop typing

## Language-Specific Guidelines
- Store all Spanish text in localization files
- Use proper accent marks and Spanish characters
- Include English translations/comments for Spanish content
- Follow Spanish language capitalization rules
- Use appropriate language tags in HTML elements

## State Management
- Use React hooks for local state
- Implement proper data fetching patterns
- Cache language-learning progress appropriately
- Handle loading and error states consistently

## Testing
- Write unit tests for utility functions
- Test language-specific edge cases
- Ensure proper handling of special characters
- Test accessibility features

## Performance
- Implement proper code splitting
- Optimize images and media content
- Use appropriate caching strategies
- Monitor and optimize bundle size
